2. What you just created (The Roadmap)
The Core (The "Manual Map" Engine)
parser/: Your RvaToOffset logic. It handles reading the DOS, NT, and Section headers from a raw buffer.

relocator/: The "Delta" math. It parses the .reloc section and patches absolute addresses so the DLL can run anywhere in memory.

resolver/: Your EAT Walker. It manually resolves DLL imports (IAT) without using GetProcAddress.

mapper/: The "Orchestrator." This file will #include the parser, relocator, and resolver to actually map the image.

The Techniques (The "Offensive" Lab)
injection/: Different ways to get your code running (APC, Remote Thread, etc.).

evasion/: This is where you put Halo's Gate and API Hashing. It’s the "Stealth" layer.

persistence/: Methods to stay on the system (Registry keys, WMI).

Common (The "Shared" Metal)
nt_structs.h: Your own definitions of PEB, LDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY, etc. (Bypassing the need for massive Windows headers).

syscall_stubs.asm: Your raw assembly for direct syscalls.

